section.div: Reaching 20 sponsors with an average of 5$, I could collect enough money in a year to buy a MacBook, so I can improve my apps and libraries even further to support iOS/macOS targets.

div.p: I'm Jeff from Germany 🇩🇪 and I am a qualified Software Developer
Take a look at my profile page or just view my repository list :)
But for a short overview you can look at my featured work below, which I either created or mainly contributed to.
Well you should sponsor me if you use and like my projects, because that's what keeps them going.

With income from GitHub sponsors, I can not only spend more time maintaining my existing projects, but also start more projects and finish them faster. Giving a sponsor also validates the work I'm doing and shows me that people believe in the code I produce and with this response I would also like to attract more people in Open Source.
div.h2: Why is OpenSource important to me?
div.p: As a passionate 🐧 Linux user, there is no getting around Open Source. Wether it's small improvements for the GNOME desktop (🖥 Dash to Dock ) or big / known / important projects in the Debian environment (📁 Nautilus ). In the Linux world, Open Source Software is not just an attitude but also a principle that everyone should actually follow. After all, we as users are also responsible for which products will be successful and, above all, which data is collected from us.
